{"video_id": "dOA9Bi8lmlo", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | Rath Yatra | 01-07-2022", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dOA9Bi8lmlo", "duration": 1835, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 14.02, "text": " ओम ज्ञानति मिरान्धस्य ज्ञानान्जनिषलाकया चक्षुरुन्मीलितं येनतस्मैश्री गुरवेनमहा नमाओमिष्णुपादाया कृष्णप्रिष्ठायभूतले"}, {"start": 14.02, "end": 29.880000000000003, "text": " श्रीमते भक्ति वेदांत स्वामिन्नितिनामिने नमस्ते सारस्वते देवे गौरवाणी प्रचारिने निर्विशेशा शून्यवादी पाश्चात्यदेशतारिने"}, {"start": 29.88, "end": 51.879999999999995, "text": " जय श्री कृष्ण चैतन्या प्रभू नित्यानन्द, श्री अद्वैत गदाधर, श्रीवासादी गौरभक्त वृन्दा, हरे कृष्ण, हरे कृष्ण, कृष्ण कृष्ण, हरे हरे, हरे राम, हरे राम, राम राम, हरे हरे।"}, {"start": 51.88, "end": 66.48, "text": " Today is the day of the Rathayatra of Lord Jagannath, Baldev and Subhadra."}, {"start": 68.32000000000001, "end": 74.76, "text": " The story of Lord Jagannath is given in this Kanda Purana."}, {"start": 76.14, "end": 79.36, "text": " I will try to narrate that story very briefly."}, {"start": 81.88, "end": 87.53999999999999, "text": " There was a king by name Indra Dhyumna, who was a great devotee of Vishnu."}, {"start": 89.38, "end": 96.39999999999999, "text": " Indra Dhyumna became very eager to meet Lord Vishnu face to face."}, {"start": 98.8, "end": 109.69999999999999, "text": " Once a Brahmana came to the palace of King Indra Dhyumna and told him about an incarnation of Lord Vishnu named Neelamadhava."}, {"start": 109.7, "end": 122.2, "text": " The king then sent different brahmanas out to search for the deity of Lord Neelamadhava."}, {"start": 122.2, "end": 132.7, "text": " They all returned unsuccessful except for one priest by name Vidyapati."}, {"start": 134.24, "end": 139.2, "text": " Vidyapati travelled for a long time."}, {"start": 139.70000000000002, "end": 147.70000000000002, "text": " After which he came to an area inhabited by non-Aryans called Shabaras."}, {"start": 149.28000000000003, "end": 155.72000000000003, "text": " He stayed at the house of a local chief whose name was Vishwavasu."}, {"start": 156.9, "end": 165.58, "text": " When he arrived, Vishwavasu was not there, but Vishwavasu's daughter Lalitha was at home."}, {"start": 167.48000000000002, "end": 169.58, "text": " Vidyapati stayed there."}, {"start": 169.70000000000002, "end": 178.92000000000002, "text": " For some time, and eventually married Lalitha, the daughter of the Shabara chief, Vishwavasu."}, {"start": 181.58, "end": 186.26000000000002, "text": " Vidyapati noticed some peculiar behavior of his host."}, {"start": 187.86, "end": 198.68, "text": " Vishwavasu would go out every day around noon and would return to the house scented with fragrance of sandalwood, camphor, and musk."}, {"start": 199.70000000000002, "end": 210.4, "text": " Vidyapati asked his wife about this and informed him that her father went to worship him."}, {"start": 210.82000000000002, "end": 218.18, "text": " Lalitha had been told by her father not to tell anyone about Neelamadhava."}, {"start": 218.18, "end": 223.24, "text": " But that was in advance of her order."}, {"start": 223.74, "end": 225.54000000000002, "text": " She was to be told by her father."}, {"start": 225.54000000000002, "end": 228.84000000000003, "text": " Lalitha else had to announced any decision."}, {"start": 228.84000000000003, "end": 229.48000000000002, "text": " By this, Linda had been pinched from mud Meela made clear her duty to his husband."}, {"start": 229.48000000000002, "end": 239.48000000000002, "text": " विद्यापती रिपीटेडली रिक्वेस्टेड तो सी नीलमाधवा।"}, {"start": 239.48000000000002, "end": 253.48000000000002, "text": " फाइनली विश्वावसु ललितास फादर बाउन्ड विद्यापतीस आईस आन्ड टुक हिम तो सी नीलमाधवा।"}, {"start": 253.48000000000002, "end": 266.48, "text": " विद्यापती सीक्रत्ली कैरिट सम्मस्टर्ड सीट्स इन इस क्लॉथ आणि ड्रॉप्ट देम अन्द पाथ आज ही वस वाकिंग।"}, {"start": 266.48, "end": 278.48, "text": " वाल ही रीच्ट नीलमाधवा द ब्लाइंटफोल्ड वस रिमोव्ड आणि विद्यापती सो नीलमाधवा।"}, {"start": 278.48, "end": 290.48, "text": " Vishwavasu went out to collect some forest flowers to worship Neelamadhava, and Vidyapati stayed near the Deity."}, {"start": 290.48, "end": 302.48, "text": " During this time, a crow fell off the branch of a tree into a nearby lake and drowned."}, {"start": 302.48, "end": 312.48, "text": " It immediately took a four-armed Vaikuntha form and started back to the spiritual world."}, {"start": 312.48, "end": 322.48, "text": " Vidyapati then climbed up onto the tree and was about to jump into the lake."}, {"start": 322.48, "end": 326.48, "text": " A voice from the sky said,"}, {"start": 326.48, "end": 332.48, "text": " Since you have seen Neelamadhava, you should inform King Indra."}, {"start": 332.48, "end": 342.48, "text": " Vishwavasu returned and started his daily worship of Neelamadhava."}, {"start": 342.48, "end": 346.48, "text": " Suddenly the Lord spoke to him and said,"}, {"start": 346.48, "end": 356.48, "text": " I have accepted many days the simple forest flowers and roots offered to me by you."}, {"start": 356.48, "end": 362.48, "text": " Now I desire the royal worship offered to me in devotion."}, {"start": 362.48, "end": 366.48, "text": " By King Indra Dhyumna."}, {"start": 366.48, "end": 372.48, "text": " Vishwavasu felt cheated by his son-in-law."}, {"start": 372.48, "end": 378.48, "text": " Therefore, he bound him up and kept in his house."}, {"start": 378.48, "end": 386.48, "text": " After repeatedly being requested by his daughter, he let him go."}, {"start": 386.48, "end": 390.48, "text": " The Brahmana, with these words, said,"}, {"start": 390.48, "end": 400.48, "text": " The Brahmana, Vidyapati, then went to King Indra Dhyumna and told him about his discovery."}, {"start": 400.48, "end": 406.48, "text": " By following the mustard seeds which had grown into small plants,"}, {"start": 406.48, "end": 412.48, "text": " they were able to follow the path to Neelamadhava."}, {"start": 412.48, "end": 418.48, "text": " When they reached the spot, they could not find him."}, {"start": 418.48, "end": 426.48, "text": " King Indra Dhyumna had the village besieged and arrested Vishwavasu."}, {"start": 426.48, "end": 434.48, "text": " Suddenly a voice from the sky told,"}, {"start": 434.48, "end": 436.48, "text": " Release the Shabara."}, {"start": 436.48, "end": 440.48, "text": " On top of Neela hill, you should construct a temple."}, {"start": 440.48, "end": 446.48, "text": " There I will manifest as Darubrahman."}, {"start": 446.48, "end": 450.48, "text": " The absolute truth manifested in a wooden form."}, {"start": 450.48, "end": 456.48, "text": " You will not see me as Neelamadhava."}, {"start": 456.48, "end": 464.48, "text": " The King Indra Dhyumna constructed a temple."}, {"start": 464.48, "end": 470.48, "text": " He wanted Lord Brahma to consecrate the temple."}, {"start": 470.48, "end": 476.48, "text": " So he travelled to Brahmaloka and waited there for him."}, {"start": 476.48, "end": 484.48, "text": " During this time, the temple became covered by sand."}, {"start": 484.48, "end": 486.48, "text": " While Indra Dhyumna was gone,"}, {"start": 486.48, "end": 500.48, "text": " first Suradeva and then Galamadhava became king of the area."}, {"start": 500.48, "end": 504.48, "text": " King Galamadhava uncovered the temple from the sand."}, {"start": 504.48, "end": 506.48, "text": " King Galamadhava uncovered the temple from the sand."}, {"start": 506.48, "end": 508.48, "text": " Shortly afterwards, King Indra Dhyumna returned from Brahma's abode."}, {"start": 508.48, "end": 514.48, "text": " Shortly afterwards, King Indra Dhyumna returned from Brahma's abode."}, {"start": 514.48, "end": 516.48, "text": " Indra Dhyumna claimed that he had built the temple."}, {"start": 516.48, "end": 518.48, "text": " Indra Dhyumna claimed that he had built the temple."}, {"start": 518.48, "end": 520.48, "text": " And Galamadhava also claimed the same thing."}, {"start": 520.48, "end": 522.48, "text": " And Galamadhava also claimed the same thing."}, {"start": 522.48, "end": 524.48, "text": " There was an old crow in the nearby banyan tree"}, {"start": 524.48, "end": 526.48, "text": " There was an old crow in the nearby banyan tree"}, {"start": 526.48, "end": 528.48, "text": " There was an old crow in the nearby banyan tree"}, {"start": 528.48, "end": 530.48, "text": " who was constantly singing the glories of Lord Rama."}, {"start": 530.48, "end": 532.48, "text": " who was constantly singing the glories of Lord Rama."}, {"start": 532.48, "end": 534.48, "text": " who was constantly singing the glories of Lord Rama."}, {"start": 534.48, "end": 549.24, "text": " The crow had seen the construction of the temple and said that Indra Dhyumna had built the temple and that Gala Madhava had just uncovered it."}, {"start": 549.24, "end": 567.24, "text": " Because he had not told the truth, Gala Madhava was ordered by Brahma to live outside the temple compound on the western side of Indra Dhyumna Sarovara lake."}, {"start": 569.24, "end": 579.24, "text": " Indra Dhyumna then asked Lord Brahma to consecrate the temple and the surrounding area which was called Sri Kshetra."}, {"start": 580.24, "end": 585.24, "text": " He gave the highest type of liberation."}, {"start": 586.24, "end": 603.24, "text": " Lord Brahma told him that Sri Kshetra is manifested by the Supreme Lord's internal potency and that the Supreme Lord manifests Himself."}, {"start": 604.24, "end": 608.24, "text": " Therefore, he could not install the Lord here."}, {"start": 610.24, "end": 616.24, "text": " Lord Jagannath and his abode are eternally situated in the material world."}, {"start": 617.24, "end": 634.24, "text": " He said he would install the flag on the temple that anyone who sees this flag and offers prostrated obeisances would easily be liberated."}, {"start": 635.24, "end": 638.24, "text": " After a while, King Indra Dhyumna became a monk."}, {"start": 640.24, "end": 643.24, "text": " King Indra Dhyumna became frustrated with not seeing Neela Madhava."}, {"start": 644.24, "end": 651.24, "text": " He decided to lay on a bed of Kusha grass and to fast until death."}, {"start": 652.24, "end": 666.24, "text": " Lord Jagannath came to him in a dream and told him that I shall come floating from the sea in my wooden form as Daru Brahman."}, {"start": 667.24, "end": 679.24, "text": " The king went to the seashore and saw a huge piece of wood which had the marks of a conch, club, disk and lotus on it."}, {"start": 680.24, "end": 686.24, "text": " Many men and elephants tried to move Daru Brahman but they could not move him."}, {"start": 687.24, "end": 693.24, "text": " That night, Lord Jagannath spoke to Indra Dhyumna in a dream"}, {"start": 693.24, "end": 705.24, "text": " and told him to bring Vishwavasu who used to serve Neela Madhava and bring a golden chariot in front of Daru Brahman."}, {"start": 706.24, "end": 712.24, "text": " The king did this and Daru Brahman easily was placed on the chariot."}, {"start": 714.24, "end": 718.24, "text": " Lord Brahma then performed a sacrifice"}, {"start": 718.24, "end": 727.24, "text": " and established a deity of Narasimha Deva on the raised platform of the sacrificial arena."}, {"start": 728.24, "end": 733.24, "text": " It is said that the deity of Narasimha in the present temple compound"}, {"start": 734.24, "end": 741.24, "text": " that is on the western side of the Mukti Mandapa is the original Narasimha deity."}, {"start": 742.24, "end": 746.24, "text": " King Indra Dhyumna had the best sculptors come"}, {"start": 746.24, "end": 751.24, "text": " to carve the deity of Lord Jagannath from Daru Brahman."}, {"start": 752.24, "end": 758.24, "text": " As soon as they started, their chisels broke to pieces."}, {"start": 759.24, "end": 767.24, "text": " Vishwakarma, the architect of the demigods, assumed a form of an old brahmana"}, {"start": 768.24, "end": 772.24, "text": " and came to Indra Dhyumna."}, {"start": 773.24, "end": 775.24, "text": " He offered to carve the deities"}, {"start": 775.24, "end": 780.24, "text": " behind closed doors for 21 days."}, {"start": 781.24, "end": 786.24, "text": " The old sculptor then took Daru Brahman into the temple"}, {"start": 787.24, "end": 789.24, "text": " and the doors were closed."}, {"start": 790.24, "end": 793.24, "text": " After 14 days passed,"}, {"start": 794.24, "end": 799.24, "text": " the king could not hear any sounds of the artist's tools"}, {"start": 800.24, "end": 804.24, "text": " and he became fully anxious."}, {"start": 806.24, "end": 814.24, "text": " The king then personally opened the door of the temple by force."}, {"start": 815.24, "end": 818.24, "text": " The king did not see the sculptor,"}, {"start": 819.24, "end": 827.24, "text": " but instead he saw the three forms of Lord Jagannath, Subhadra and Lord Balarama."}, {"start": 828.24, "end": 832.24, "text": " Their fingers and toes were unfinished."}, {"start": 832.24, "end": 835.24, "text": " Thinking himself a great offender,"}, {"start": 836.24, "end": 839.24, "text": " the king decided to give up his life."}, {"start": 840.24, "end": 845.24, "text": " He then laid on a bed of kushagras and began to fast."}, {"start": 846.24, "end": 850.24, "text": " Lord Jagannath appeared to him in a dream."}, {"start": 851.24, "end": 853.24, "text": " Lord Jagannath told the king,"}, {"start": 854.24, "end": 857.24, "text": " I am eternally situated here in Nilachala"}, {"start": 857.24, "end": 861.24, "text": " in the form of Lord Jagannath as Daru Brahman."}, {"start": 862.24, "end": 865.24, "text": " I have no material hands and feet,"}, {"start": 866.24, "end": 869.24, "text": " but with my transcendental senses"}, {"start": 870.24, "end": 875.24, "text": " I accept all the items offered by my devotees."}, {"start": 876.24, "end": 879.24, "text": " The fact that you broke your promise"}, {"start": 880.24, "end": 883.24, "text": " is a part of the pastime for me"}, {"start": 883.24, "end": 887.24, "text": " to manifest in the form of Jagannath."}, {"start": 888.24, "end": 895.24, "text": " Those devotees whose eyes are smeared with the salve of love"}, {"start": 896.24, "end": 901.24, "text": " will always see me as Shamasundara holding a flute."}, {"start": 904.24, "end": 907.24, "text": " The king then prayed to Lord Jagannath"}, {"start": 908.24, "end": 911.24, "text": " that those in the family of the sculptor"}, {"start": 911.24, "end": 913.24, "text": " who manifested his form"}, {"start": 914.24, "end": 917.24, "text": " will continue to assist in constructing the three"}, {"start": 918.24, "end": 922.24, "text": " karts, the three rathas."}, {"start": 923.24, "end": 925.24, "text": " He also told the king"}, {"start": 926.24, "end": 928.24, "text": " that the descendants of Vishwavasu"}, {"start": 929.24, "end": 931.24, "text": " who served him as Neelamadhava"}, {"start": 932.24, "end": 936.24, "text": " should generation after generation serve the Lord."}, {"start": 937.24, "end": 940.24, "text": " They shall be called Daitas."}, {"start": 941.24, "end": 943.24, "text": " The descendants of Vidyavati"}, {"start": 944.24, "end": 946.24, "text": " born from his brahmana wife"}, {"start": 947.24, "end": 949.24, "text": " should perform the deity worship."}, {"start": 951.24, "end": 955.24, "text": " The descendants born from his shabara wife Lalitha"}, {"start": 956.24, "end": 958.24, "text": " should cook the Lord's food."}, {"start": 959.24, "end": 961.24, "text": " King Indrajumna"}, {"start": 962.24, "end": 964.24, "text": " then requested Lord Jagannath"}, {"start": 965.24, "end": 967.24, "text": " that the doors of the temple"}, {"start": 967.24, "end": 971.24, "text": " should be closed only three hours a day."}, {"start": 972.24, "end": 974.24, "text": " The king also requested"}, {"start": 975.24, "end": 978.24, "text": " that he would not have any descendants"}, {"start": 979.24, "end": 981.24, "text": " so that no one in the future"}, {"start": 982.24, "end": 984.24, "text": " would claim the temple of Lord Jagannath"}, {"start": 985.24, "end": 987.24, "text": " as their own property."}, {"start": 989.24, "end": 991.24, "text": " This is the story"}, {"start": 992.24, "end": 995.24, "text": " of the appearance of Lord Jagannath."}, {"start": 997.24, "end": 1000.24, "text": " Now there is also a description"}, {"start": 1001.24, "end": 1006.24, "text": " of Jagannath being"}, {"start": 1007.24, "end": 1011.24, "text": " the ecstatic form of Lord Krishna himself."}, {"start": 1014.24, "end": 1017.24, "text": " Once during a solar eclipse"}, {"start": 1018.24, "end": 1020.24, "text": " Krishna, Balaram, Subhadra"}, {"start": 1021.24, "end": 1023.24, "text": " and other residents of Dwarka"}, {"start": 1024.24, "end": 1026.24, "text": " went to bathe in a holy pond"}, {"start": 1026.24, "end": 1027.24, "text": " at Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 1028.24, "end": 1030.24, "text": " Knowing that Krishna would be there"}, {"start": 1031.24, "end": 1033.24, "text": " Srimati Radharani, Krishna's parents"}, {"start": 1034.24, "end": 1035.24, "text": " Nanda Nishoda"}, {"start": 1036.24, "end": 1037.24, "text": " and other residents of Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1038.24, "end": 1039.24, "text": " who were burning in the fire"}, {"start": 1040.24, "end": 1041.24, "text": " of separation from the Lord"}, {"start": 1042.24, "end": 1043.24, "text": " went to meet him."}, {"start": 1044.24, "end": 1047.24, "text": " Inside one of the many tents"}, {"start": 1048.24, "end": 1050.24, "text": " the pilgrims had set up at Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 1051.24, "end": 1053.24, "text": " Rohini, Lord Balaram's mother"}, {"start": 1053.24, "end": 1056.24, "text": " narrated Krishna's Vrindavan pastimes"}, {"start": 1057.24, "end": 1059.24, "text": " to the queens of Dwarka"}, {"start": 1060.24, "end": 1063.24, "text": " and other Dwarka Nivasis."}, {"start": 1065.24, "end": 1067.24, "text": " The residents of Dwarka are said to be"}, {"start": 1068.24, "end": 1070.24, "text": " in the mood of opulence or Aishwarya"}, {"start": 1071.24, "end": 1073.24, "text": " and they worship Krishna"}, {"start": 1074.24, "end": 1076.24, "text": " as the Supreme Lord."}, {"start": 1077.24, "end": 1079.24, "text": " But the residents of Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1080.24, "end": 1082.24, "text": " are in the mood of sweetness, Madhurya"}, {"start": 1083.24, "end": 1085.24, "text": " and they have a confidential relationship"}, {"start": 1086.24, "end": 1087.24, "text": " with Krishna"}, {"start": 1088.24, "end": 1090.24, "text": " that surpasses awe and reverence"}, {"start": 1091.24, "end": 1095.24, "text": " because it is based on friendship and love."}, {"start": 1096.24, "end": 1101.24, "text": " Rohini's narration was thus extremely confidential"}, {"start": 1102.24, "end": 1106.24, "text": " so she posted Subhadra at the door"}, {"start": 1107.24, "end": 1110.24, "text": " to prevent anyone from entering."}, {"start": 1110.24, "end": 1114.24, "text": " Krishna and Balaram came to the door"}, {"start": 1115.24, "end": 1118.24, "text": " and stood on Subhadra's left and right sides."}, {"start": 1119.24, "end": 1122.24, "text": " While listening to Rohini's narration"}, {"start": 1123.24, "end": 1125.24, "text": " of Krishna's intimate Vrindavan pastimes"}, {"start": 1126.24, "end": 1128.24, "text": " Krishna and Balaram became ecstatic"}, {"start": 1129.24, "end": 1131.24, "text": " and their internal feelings"}, {"start": 1132.24, "end": 1135.24, "text": " were exhibited externally."}, {"start": 1136.24, "end": 1139.24, "text": " Their eyes became dilated."}, {"start": 1140.24, "end": 1142.24, "text": " Their limbs became retracted."}, {"start": 1143.24, "end": 1145.24, "text": " Seeing these transformations"}, {"start": 1146.24, "end": 1148.24, "text": " in Krishna and Balaram"}, {"start": 1149.24, "end": 1151.24, "text": " Subhadra also became ecstatic"}, {"start": 1152.24, "end": 1154.24, "text": " and assumed a similar form."}, {"start": 1156.24, "end": 1161.24, "text": " Thus, by hearing about Krishna's pastimes in Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1162.24, "end": 1163.24, "text": " Krishna and Balaram"}, {"start": 1164.24, "end": 1166.24, "text": " with Subhadra in between"}, {"start": 1167.24, "end": 1169.24, "text": " displayed their ecstatic forms"}, {"start": 1170.24, "end": 1171.24, "text": " of Jagannath,"}, {"start": 1172.24, "end": 1173.24, "text": " Baladeva"}, {"start": 1174.24, "end": 1175.24, "text": " and Subhadra."}, {"start": 1179.24, "end": 1180.24, "text": " When the sage Narada"}, {"start": 1181.24, "end": 1183.24, "text": " saw Krishna transformed as Jagannath"}, {"start": 1184.24, "end": 1186.24, "text": " he prayed to the Lord"}, {"start": 1187.24, "end": 1189.24, "text": " to appear like this again."}, {"start": 1191.24, "end": 1194.24, "text": " Although the Lord is not obliged to anyone"}, {"start": 1196.24, "end": 1198.24, "text": " he reciprocates with his devotees"}, {"start": 1198.24, "end": 1201.24, "text": " to fulfil their desires."}, {"start": 1202.24, "end": 1205.24, "text": " Thus, just as Krishna appeared as"}, {"start": 1206.24, "end": 1209.24, "text": " Neela Madhava to satisfy Vishwavasu"}, {"start": 1210.24, "end": 1214.24, "text": " he appeared in the Deity form as Jagannath"}, {"start": 1215.24, "end": 1218.24, "text": " and resides in Jagannath Puri"}, {"start": 1219.24, "end": 1222.24, "text": " to satisfy the desire of Narada Muni."}, {"start": 1223.24, "end": 1226.24, "text": " This special form of Krishna"}, {"start": 1226.24, "end": 1228.24, "text": " is also known as Patitapavana"}, {"start": 1229.24, "end": 1231.24, "text": " the saviour of the fallen"}, {"start": 1232.24, "end": 1234.24, "text": " and anyone who takes his audience"}, {"start": 1235.24, "end": 1237.24, "text": " with proper consciousness"}, {"start": 1238.24, "end": 1241.24, "text": " is awarded spiritual liberation."}, {"start": 1243.24, "end": 1246.24, "text": " It is said in the Narada Purana"}, {"start": 1247.24, "end": 1251.24, "text": " in that great abode known as Purushottam Kshetra"}, {"start": 1252.24, "end": 1255.24, "text": " which is rarely achieved among all the three"}, {"start": 1256.24, "end": 1257.24, "text": " worlds"}, {"start": 1258.24, "end": 1259.24, "text": " the Keshava Deity"}, {"start": 1260.24, "end": 1263.24, "text": " who was fashioned by the Supreme Lord himself"}, {"start": 1263.24, "end": 1265.24, "text": " is situated."}, {"start": 1266.24, "end": 1269.24, "text": " If men simply see that Deity"}, {"start": 1270.24, "end": 1274.24, "text": " they are easily able to go to the Lord's abode."}, {"start": 1279.24, "end": 1281.24, "text": " There is also"}, {"start": 1282.24, "end": 1283.24, "text": " a narration"}, {"start": 1284.24, "end": 1285.24, "text": " in the"}, {"start": 1285.24, "end": 1286.24, "text": " Krishna book"}, {"start": 1287.24, "end": 1291.24, "text": " about the origin of Jagannath Rathayatra."}, {"start": 1294.24, "end": 1295.24, "text": " Once upon a time"}, {"start": 1296.24, "end": 1299.24, "text": " while Lord Krishna and Balarama were living peacefully"}, {"start": 1299.24, "end": 1301.24, "text": " in their great city of Dwaraka"}, {"start": 1302.24, "end": 1304.24, "text": " there was the rare occasion"}, {"start": 1304.24, "end": 1306.24, "text": " of a full solar eclipse"}, {"start": 1307.24, "end": 1309.24, "text": " such as takes place"}, {"start": 1309.24, "end": 1311.24, "text": " at the end of every Kalpa"}, {"start": 1311.24, "end": 1313.24, "text": " or day of Brahma."}, {"start": 1315.24, "end": 1317.24, "text": " By astronomical calculation"}, {"start": 1318.24, "end": 1321.24, "text": " people were informed about this great eclipse"}, {"start": 1321.24, "end": 1323.24, "text": " prior to its taking place."}, {"start": 1324.24, "end": 1326.24, "text": " Therefore everyone"}, {"start": 1326.24, "end": 1327.24, "text": " both men and women"}, {"start": 1328.24, "end": 1329.24, "text": " decided to assemble"}, {"start": 1330.24, "end": 1332.24, "text": " at the holy place in Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 1333.24, "end": 1334.24, "text": " known as"}, {"start": 1334.24, "end": 1336.24, "text": " Samantapanjaka."}, {"start": 1337.24, "end": 1340.24, "text": " After arriving in Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 1341.24, "end": 1342.24, "text": " the members of the Yadu dynasty"}, {"start": 1342.24, "end": 1345.24, "text": " took their baths ceremoniously"}, {"start": 1345.24, "end": 1347.24, "text": " with self-control"}, {"start": 1347.24, "end": 1349.24, "text": " as enjoined in the Shastras"}, {"start": 1349.24, "end": 1351.24, "text": " and they observed fasting"}, {"start": 1351.24, "end": 1353.24, "text": " for the whole period of the eclipse"}, {"start": 1353.24, "end": 1355.24, "text": " in order to nullify the reactions"}, {"start": 1355.24, "end": 1358.24, "text": " of their sinful activities."}, {"start": 1359.24, "end": 1361.24, "text": " The ceremonial functions"}, {"start": 1361.24, "end": 1364.24, "text": " performed by the members of the Yadu dynasty"}, {"start": 1364.24, "end": 1366.24, "text": " externally"}, {"start": 1366.24, "end": 1368.24, "text": " resemble the ritualistic ceremonies"}, {"start": 1368.24, "end": 1370.24, "text": " performed by the Karmis."}, {"start": 1370.24, "end": 1372.24, "text": " When a Karmi performs"}, {"start": 1372.24, "end": 1374.24, "text": " some ritualistic ceremonies"}, {"start": 1374.24, "end": 1375.24, "text": " ambition is"}, {"start": 1375.24, "end": 1377.24, "text": " self-gratification"}, {"start": 1377.24, "end": 1378.24, "text": " good position"}, {"start": 1378.24, "end": 1379.24, "text": " good wife"}, {"start": 1379.24, "end": 1380.24, "text": " good house"}, {"start": 1380.24, "end": 1381.24, "text": " good children"}, {"start": 1381.24, "end": 1382.24, "text": " or good wealth."}, {"start": 1383.24, "end": 1384.24, "text": " But the ambition"}, {"start": 1384.24, "end": 1386.24, "text": " of the members of the Yadu dynasty"}, {"start": 1386.24, "end": 1388.24, "text": " was different."}, {"start": 1389.24, "end": 1390.24, "text": " Their ambition"}, {"start": 1390.24, "end": 1392.24, "text": " was to offer Krishna"}, {"start": 1392.24, "end": 1394.24, "text": " perpetual devotion"}, {"start": 1394.24, "end": 1396.24, "text": " with faith."}, {"start": 1397.24, "end": 1398.24, "text": " All the members"}, {"start": 1398.24, "end": 1399.24, "text": " of the Yadu dynasty"}, {"start": 1399.24, "end": 1403.24, "text": " were great devotees of Krishna."}, {"start": 1405.24, "end": 1406.24, "text": " When Nanda Maharaj"}, {"start": 1406.24, "end": 1408.24, "text": " and other residents of Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1408.24, "end": 1409.24, "text": " had heard"}, {"start": 1409.24, "end": 1410.24, "text": " that Krishna would be present"}, {"start": 1410.24, "end": 1412.24, "text": " in Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 1412.24, "end": 1414.24, "text": " because of the solar eclipse"}, {"start": 1414.24, "end": 1416.24, "text": " and that all the members"}, {"start": 1416.24, "end": 1417.24, "text": " of the Yadu dynasty"}, {"start": 1417.24, "end": 1418.24, "text": " would also be there"}, {"start": 1419.24, "end": 1420.24, "text": " they had immediately"}, {"start": 1420.24, "end": 1422.24, "text": " prepared to go there."}, {"start": 1423.24, "end": 1424.24, "text": " King Nanda accompanied"}, {"start": 1424.24, "end": 1426.24, "text": " by his cowherd men"}, {"start": 1426.24, "end": 1428.24, "text": " had loaded all their necessary"}, {"start": 1428.24, "end": 1430.24, "text": " paraphernalia and bullock carts"}, {"start": 1431.24, "end": 1433.24, "text": " and all of their Vrindavan residents"}, {"start": 1433.24, "end": 1435.24, "text": " had come to Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 1436.24, "end": 1438.24, "text": " to see their beloved sons"}, {"start": 1438.24, "end": 1439.24, "text": " Lord Balaram"}, {"start": 1439.24, "end": 1440.24, "text": " and Lord Krishna."}, {"start": 1442.24, "end": 1443.24, "text": " When the cowherd men"}, {"start": 1443.24, "end": 1444.24, "text": " of Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1444.24, "end": 1445.24, "text": " arrived in Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 1446.24, "end": 1447.24, "text": " all the Yadu"}, {"start": 1449.24, "end": 1451.24, "text": " dynasty members"}, {"start": 1451.24, "end": 1453.24, "text": " were most pleased."}, {"start": 1454.24, "end": 1455.24, "text": " As soon as they saw"}, {"start": 1455.24, "end": 1457.24, "text": " the residents of Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1457.24, "end": 1459.24, "text": " they stood up to welcome them"}, {"start": 1459.24, "end": 1460.24, "text": " and appeared to have"}, {"start": 1460.24, "end": 1462.24, "text": " regained their life."}, {"start": 1463.24, "end": 1464.24, "text": " All the Yadus"}, {"start": 1464.24, "end": 1466.24, "text": " and Vrindavan residents"}, {"start": 1466.24, "end": 1467.24, "text": " had been very eager"}, {"start": 1467.24, "end": 1469.24, "text": " to meet each other"}, {"start": 1470.24, "end": 1471.24, "text": " and when they actually"}, {"start": 1471.24, "end": 1473.24, "text": " came forward and met"}, {"start": 1473.24, "end": 1475.24, "text": " they embraced one another"}, {"start": 1475.24, "end": 1477.24, "text": " to their heart's satisfaction"}, {"start": 1477.24, "end": 1479.24, "text": " and remained in embrace"}, {"start": 1479.24, "end": 1481.24, "text": " for a considerable time."}, {"start": 1482.24, "end": 1483.24, "text": " As far as the gopis"}, {"start": 1483.24, "end": 1485.24, "text": " of Vrindavan were concerned"}, {"start": 1485.24, "end": 1487.24, "text": " from the very beginning"}, {"start": 1487.24, "end": 1488.24, "text": " of their lives"}, {"start": 1488.24, "end": 1489.24, "text": " they did not know"}, {"start": 1489.24, "end": 1491.24, "text": " anything beyond Krishna."}, {"start": 1492.24, "end": 1494.24, "text": " Krishna and Balaram"}, {"start": 1494.24, "end": 1496.24, "text": " were their life and soul."}, {"start": 1497.24, "end": 1498.24, "text": " The gopis were so attached"}, {"start": 1498.24, "end": 1499.24, "text": " to Krishna"}, {"start": 1499.24, "end": 1500.24, "text": " that they could not"}, {"start": 1500.24, "end": 1501.24, "text": " even tolerate"}, {"start": 1501.24, "end": 1504.24, "text": " not seeing him momentarily"}, {"start": 1504.24, "end": 1506.24, "text": " when their eyelids blinked"}, {"start": 1507.24, "end": 1509.24, "text": " and impeded their vision."}, {"start": 1510.24, "end": 1512.24, "text": " They condemned Brahma"}, {"start": 1513.24, "end": 1515.24, "text": " the creator of the body"}, {"start": 1515.24, "end": 1516.24, "text": " because"}, {"start": 1516.24, "end": 1518.24, "text": " he foolishly made eyelids"}, {"start": 1518.24, "end": 1520.24, "text": " which blinked"}, {"start": 1520.24, "end": 1523.24, "text": " and checked their seeing Krishna."}, {"start": 1524.24, "end": 1526.24, "text": " Because they had been separated"}, {"start": 1526.24, "end": 1529.24, "text": " from Krishna for so many years"}, {"start": 1529.24, "end": 1532.24, "text": " the gopis having come along"}, {"start": 1532.24, "end": 1533.24, "text": " with Nanda Maharaj"}, {"start": 1533.24, "end": 1535.24, "text": " and Mother Yashoda"}, {"start": 1535.24, "end": 1538.24, "text": " felt intense ecstasy"}, {"start": 1538.24, "end": 1540.24, "text": " upon seeing Krishna."}, {"start": 1541.24, "end": 1543.24, "text": " No one can imagine"}, {"start": 1543.24, "end": 1545.24, "text": " how eager the gopis"}, {"start": 1545.24, "end": 1549.24, "text": " were to see Krishna again."}, {"start": 1550.24, "end": 1551.24, "text": " As soon as Krishna"}, {"start": 1551.24, "end": 1553.24, "text": " became visible to them"}, {"start": 1553.24, "end": 1556.24, "text": " they took him inside their hearts"}, {"start": 1556.24, "end": 1559.24, "text": " through their eyes"}, {"start": 1559.24, "end": 1561.24, "text": " and embraced him"}, {"start": 1561.24, "end": 1563.24, "text": " to their full satisfaction."}, {"start": 1564.24, "end": 1565.24, "text": " Even though they were"}, {"start": 1565.24, "end": 1568.24, "text": " embracing Krishna only mentally"}, {"start": 1568.24, "end": 1570.24, "text": " they became so ecstatic"}, {"start": 1570.24, "end": 1572.24, "text": " and overwhelmed with joy"}, {"start": 1572.24, "end": 1574.24, "text": " that for the time being"}, {"start": 1574.24, "end": 1578.24, "text": " they completely forgot themselves."}, {"start": 1580.24, "end": 1581.24, "text": " The ecstatic trance"}, {"start": 1581.24, "end": 1583.24, "text": " they achieved simply"}, {"start": 1583.24, "end": 1585.24, "text": " by mentally embracing Krishna"}, {"start": 1585.24, "end": 1588.24, "text": " is impossible to achieve"}, {"start": 1588.24, "end": 1590.24, "text": " even for great yogis"}, {"start": 1590.24, "end": 1593.24, "text": " constantly engaged in meditation"}, {"start": 1593.24, "end": 1596.24, "text": " on the Supreme Personality of Godhead."}, {"start": 1597.24, "end": 1599.24, "text": " Krishna could understand"}, {"start": 1599.24, "end": 1601.24, "text": " that the gopis were wrapped in ecstasy"}, {"start": 1601.24, "end": 1603.24, "text": " by embracing him in their minds"}, {"start": 1603.24, "end": 1605.24, "text": " and therefore"}, {"start": 1605.24, "end": 1606.24, "text": " since he is present"}, {"start": 1606.24, "end": 1608.24, "text": " in everyone's heart"}, {"start": 1608.24, "end": 1609.24, "text": " he reciprocated"}, {"start": 1609.24, "end": 1612.24, "text": " the embracing from within."}, {"start": 1614.24, "end": 1615.24, "text": " Krishna was sitting"}, {"start": 1615.24, "end": 1616.24, "text": " with Mother Yashoda"}, {"start": 1616.24, "end": 1617.24, "text": " and his other mothers"}, {"start": 1617.24, "end": 1619.24, "text": " Devaki and Rohini"}, {"start": 1619.24, "end": 1620.24, "text": " but when the mothers"}, {"start": 1620.24, "end": 1622.24, "text": " engaged in talking"}, {"start": 1622.24, "end": 1625.24, "text": " he took the opportunity"}, {"start": 1625.24, "end": 1628.24, "text": " and went to a secluded place"}, {"start": 1628.24, "end": 1630.24, "text": " to meet the gopis."}, {"start": 1631.24, "end": 1632.24, "text": " As soon as he approached"}, {"start": 1632.24, "end": 1633.24, "text": " the gopis"}, {"start": 1633.24, "end": 1635.24, "text": " the Lord smiled"}, {"start": 1635.24, "end": 1637.24, "text": " and after embracing them"}, {"start": 1637.24, "end": 1640.24, "text": " and inquiring about their welfare"}, {"start": 1640.24, "end": 1642.24, "text": " he began to encourage them"}, {"start": 1642.24, "end": 1643.24, "text": " saying"}, {"start": 1643.24, "end": 1644.24, "text": " my dear friends"}, {"start": 1644.24, "end": 1646.24, "text": " you know that Lord Balaram"}, {"start": 1646.24, "end": 1648.24, "text": " and I left Rundhavan"}, {"start": 1648.24, "end": 1649.24, "text": " just to please our relatives"}, {"start": 1649.24, "end": 1651.24, "text": " and family members."}, {"start": 1651.24, "end": 1653.24, "text": " Thus we were long engaged"}, {"start": 1653.24, "end": 1655.24, "text": " in fighting with our enemies"}, {"start": 1655.24, "end": 1658.24, "text": " and were obliged to forget you"}, {"start": 1658.24, "end": 1661.24, "text": " who were so much attached to me"}, {"start": 1661.24, "end": 1664.24, "text": " in love and affection."}, {"start": 1664.24, "end": 1665.24, "text": " I can understand"}, {"start": 1665.24, "end": 1668.24, "text": " that I have been ungrateful to you"}, {"start": 1668.24, "end": 1669.24, "text": " but still I know"}, {"start": 1669.24, "end": 1671.24, "text": " that you are faithful to me."}, {"start": 1671.24, "end": 1673.24, "text": " May I inquire"}, {"start": 1673.24, "end": 1675.24, "text": " if you have been thinking of us"}, {"start": 1675.24, "end": 1678.24, "text": " although we had to leave you behind?"}, {"start": 1678.24, "end": 1680.24, "text": " My dear gopis"}, {"start": 1680.24, "end": 1683.24, "text": " do you not dislike remembering me"}, {"start": 1683.24, "end": 1687.24, "text": " considering me to have been ungrateful to you?"}, {"start": 1687.24, "end": 1689.24, "text": " Do you take my misbehavior"}, {"start": 1689.24, "end": 1691.24, "text": " with you very seriously?"}, {"start": 1691.24, "end": 1693.24, "text": " Fortunately"}, {"start": 1693.24, "end": 1695.24, "text": " you have developed loving affection for me"}, {"start": 1695.24, "end": 1697.24, "text": " which is the only way"}, {"start": 1697.24, "end": 1700.24, "text": " to achieve the transcendental position"}, {"start": 1700.24, "end": 1703.24, "text": " of association with me."}, {"start": 1710.24, "end": 1713.24, "text": " Lord Krishna concluded by saying"}, {"start": 1713.24, "end": 1716.24, "text": " unalloyed devotional service"}, {"start": 1716.24, "end": 1718.24, "text": " and affection for me"}, {"start": 1718.24, "end": 1721.24, "text": " are the cause of supreme liberation."}, {"start": 1721.24, "end": 1733.24, "text": " The gopis responded to Krishna"}, {"start": 1733.24, "end": 1735.24, "text": " by saying"}, {"start": 1735.24, "end": 1737.24, "text": " My dear Krishna"}, {"start": 1737.24, "end": 1740.24, "text": " we therefore request that"}, {"start": 1740.24, "end": 1742.24, "text": " you remain within our hearts"}, {"start": 1742.24, "end": 1744.24, "text": " as the rising sun"}, {"start": 1744.24, "end": 1747.24, "text": " that will be your greatest benediction."}, {"start": 1751.24, "end": 1759.24, "text": " The gopis are always liberated souls"}, {"start": 1759.24, "end": 1762.24, "text": " because they are always in Krishna consciousness."}, {"start": 1762.24, "end": 1765.24, "text": " They only pretended to be entangled"}, {"start": 1765.24, "end": 1767.24, "text": " in the household affairs in Vrindavan."}, {"start": 1770.24, "end": 1773.24, "text": " Because of their separation from Krishna"}, {"start": 1773.24, "end": 1775.24, "text": " he might have asked them"}, {"start": 1775.24, "end": 1777.24, "text": " to return with him to Dwarka"}, {"start": 1777.24, "end": 1779.24, "text": " but the inhabitants of Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1779.24, "end": 1780.24, "text": " the gopis"}, {"start": 1780.24, "end": 1782.24, "text": " were not interested in the idea"}, {"start": 1782.24, "end": 1784.24, "text": " of going with Krishna to Dwarka."}, {"start": 1786.24, "end": 1789.24, "text": " They wanted to remain in Vrindavan"}, {"start": 1789.24, "end": 1792.24, "text": " and thus feel the presence of Krishna"}, {"start": 1792.24, "end": 1794.24, "text": " in every step of their lives."}, {"start": 1794.24, "end": 1798.24, "text": " This transcendental emotional existence"}, {"start": 1798.24, "end": 1799.24, "text": " of the gopis"}, {"start": 1799.24, "end": 1800.24, "text": " is the basic principle"}, {"start": 1800.24, "end": 1802.24, "text": " of Lord Chaitanya's teachings."}, {"start": 1803.24, "end": 1805.24, "text": " The Rathayatra festival"}, {"start": 1805.24, "end": 1807.24, "text": " observed by Lord Chaitanya"}, {"start": 1807.24, "end": 1810.24, "text": " is the emotional process of taking Krishna"}, {"start": 1810.24, "end": 1812.24, "text": " back to Vrindavan."}, {"start": 1812.24, "end": 1814.24, "text": " Srimati Radharani refused"}, {"start": 1814.24, "end": 1816.24, "text": " to go with Krishna to Dwarka"}, {"start": 1816.24, "end": 1817.24, "text": " to enjoy his company"}, {"start": 1817.24, "end": 1820.24, "text": " in the atmosphere of royal opulence"}, {"start": 1820.24, "end": 1824.24, "text": " for she wanted to enjoy his company"}, {"start": 1824.24, "end": 1828.24, "text": " in the original Vrindavan atmosphere."}, {"start": 1831.24, "end": 1832.24, "text": " I'll stop here."}, {"start": 1832.24, "end": 1833.24, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 1833.24, "end": 1834.24, "text": " Hare Krishna."}]}